# BMI Calculator
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10%2B-blue) ![Jupyter](https://img.shields.io/badge/Jupyter-Notebook-orange) ![Amazon-Prep](https://img.shields.io/badge/Built%20for-Amazon%20Internship-FF9900)
A beginner-friendly **BMI Calculator** built in Python.
This program calculates BMI for 3 people, classifies results using WHO standards, and saves all reports to a text file.

---

## About
This project demonstrates core python concepts.
- **Loops** 'for' - Process 3 users automatically.
- **Conditionals**  'if-elif-else' - Classify BMI categories.
- **File handling** 'with open()' - Saves persistent reports.
- **F-strings** - Clean, readable output.

---

### Features
- Takes input for 3 people: name, age, weight, height
- Calculates BMI using metric formula:'BMI = weight / height_m)2'
- Classifies BMI using WHO standards
- Saves formatted reports to 'bmi_reports.txt'
- Clean console output with personalized feedback

---

### BMI Classification (WHO Standards)
| Range (BMI) |Category| Health Risk |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Below 18.5 | Underweight | Minimal |
| 18.5 -24.9 | Normal weight | Low |
|25.0 - 29.9 | Overweight | Increased |
|30.0 + | Obese | High |

